# ── THE ONLY RULE THAT MATTERS HERE ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Your PROFILE is the one file with all your personal facts in one place.
# It is NOT supposed to live in this repo — it belongs on your task list, as a
# row labelled `cos-profile`. But if you ever fill the template in place, or
# drop a copy here "just for a second", these patterns stop it reaching a public
# remote. This is a guard, not a permission.
PROFILE.md
profile.md
PROFILE-*.md
**/PROFILE.md
!references/PROFILE.template.md

# A live MCP config points at YOUR machine's paths and may hold secrets.
# The tracked file is mcp.example.json — that one is safe and inert.
.mcp.json
mcp.json
!mcp.example.json

# Secrets, in every shape people accidentally commit them.
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*_rsa
credentials.json
token.json
*.secret

# Anything you were told to keep local.
/local/
/private/
/scratch/
*.local.md

# OS / editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
